#subtitle: Building relations with the other political parties of Germany.

= Inter-Party Relationships

The SPD cannot govern alone. In fact, the SPD cannot and and shouldn't govern, period, but we are not ready to acknowledge that yet. Because we do not have any electoral majority, competence, or class consciousness, we need to be told what to do by other parties. Recently, our governments have consisted of the Weimar Coalition of the SPD, Center, and Democratic parties. We can reach out and build additional connections with these parties, or perhaps we can stand alone.

- @liberals: Strengthen our bonds with the conservatives of German Democratic Party and reactionaries of German People's Party.
- @center: Strengthen our bonds with the Catholic Center Party cult.
- @kpd: Work towards repairing relationships with the Communist Party.
- @spd_alone: The SPD has burned too many bridges and must stand alone.
- @easy_discard


